==English==

===Etymology===
Middle French ''democratie'' < Medieval Latin ''democratia'' < Greek [[δημοκράτια]] < [[δήμος]] (common people) < Proto-Indo-European '''*da-mo-''' (division) < PIE base '''*da-''' (to divide, to cut up) + Greek [[κράτος]] (rule, strength) < Proto-Indo-European '''*kratus''' (strength).

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-y|democrac|y}}

# Rule by the people.
# {{cattag|Government}} A [[Government]] under the direct or representative rule of the [[people]] of its jurisdiction.
# Belief in political freedom and equality.

